approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `amount` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5.05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the value {ERC20} uses, unless this function is overridden; NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

params.amount: Amount of payment token in the deposit

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

returns.pTokenPayout: Amount of the payment token to be transfered
returns.rTokenPayout: Amount of the reward token to be transfered

params.depositor: Address of the user making deposit

returns.newlySyncedShares: Preview of new Silica Vault tokens after calculation
returns.unredeemedShares: Preview of new unredeemed Silica Vault tokens after deposit

processWithdraws().details: This is the first step in rollover to next round

returns.paymentLockup: Amount of payment token locked for the withdrawals
returns.rewardLockup: Amount of reward token locked for the withdrawals

params.amount: amount of payment token to exchange for Silica

params.shares: Amount of Silica Vault token to redeem

returns.paymentPayout: Amount of payment token to transfer
returns.rewardPayout: Amount of reward token to transfer

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.shares: Amount of Silica Vault token to withdraw

params.silicaAddress: The address of defaulted Silica to settle

returns.paymentPayout: The amount of payment token returned

params.silicaAddress: The address of finished Silica to settle

params.defaultedSilicas: Addresses of defaulted contracts to settle
params.finishedSilicas: Addresses of finished contracts to settle

startNextRound(uint256).details: Must be last step after processing withdraws and swapping

params.epochDuration: The length of the new epoch

returns.mintedShares: The newly minted Silica Vault token from the new deposit

params.contractTrader: Adapter contract to use trading platform
params.data: The call data for this transaction
params.paymentTraded: Amount of the payment token traded in

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

totalPaymentHeld().details: Excludes outstanding debt in payment tokens and pending payment deposits

totalRewardHeld().details: Excludes outstanding debt in reward tokens

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

deposit(uint256).notice: Mints Silica Vault token to msg.sender by depositing payment token

getCurrentRound().notice: Return the current epoch number of the Silica Vault

getCurrentRoundEndDay().notice: Return the then day of current epoch

getLastDayForSettlements().notice: Return the last day of the settlement period of this epoch

getNumSilicasActive().notice: Return the total number of Running state Silica

getPTokenLocked().notice: Return the total payment token locked in the Silica Vault

getPendingDeposits().notice: Return the total pending deposit for next epoch

getRTokenLocked().notice: Return the total reward token locked in the SIlica Vault

getSharesPendingBurn().notice: Return the number of pending shares to be burn at the end of epoch

getSilicaType().notice: Return the type of Silica that the vault manages         Please refer to commodity type in Documentation

getWithdrawalsOpen().notice: Return true if the SIlica Vault accepts withdrawal request

isTerminated().notice: Return true if the Silica Vault is terminated

previewProcessScheduledWithdraw().notice: Return a preview of the result of the withdrawal

previewSyncShares(address).notice: Return a preview for a user after the deposit is in vault      Please refer to documentation for roll-over calculation

processWithdraws().notice: Process all pending withdraw requests from the previous round

purchaseSilica(address,uint256).notice: Admin calls this function purchase as of Vault

redeem(uint256).notice: Redeem Silica Vault token based on user's position in the vault

redeemMax().notice: Redeem maximum of Silica Vault token to a user

redeemWithdrawRequest().notice: Processes a scheduled withdrawal from a previous round. Redeem reward and payment tokens

scheduleWithdraw(uint256).notice: Schedules a withdrawal of Silica Vault Tokens that can be processed once the round completes

startNextRound(uint256).notice: Processes all pending deposits and kicks off next epoch

swap(address,uint256,bytes).notice: Admin swaps reward token with payment token

terminate().notice: Admin to terminate the Silica Vault

totalPaymentHeld().notice: Returns payment tokens held by the vault

totalRewardHeld().notice: Returns reward tokens held by the vault
